\ud83e\udd40 \n\nMiami-based Haitian American artist Ruth Burotte is known professionally as RUTAMFI. Born in 1998 in Queens, NY, and raised in Forest Park, GA, RUTAMFI is a multidisciplinary artist whose practice spans character design, public art, and immersive installations. With a BFA in Art & Technology from New World School of the Arts at the University of Florida, RUTAMFI blends traditional watercolor with digital media, creating stylized works that explore identity, technology, and society. Since 2018, she has played an integral role in Miami\u2019s art scene, contributing to local and public art projects that reflect her humor and unique perspective.\n\nHer new work, Rose Tinted, builds directly on the skills and vision she developed in MAD Arts\u2019 Projection Mapping Workshop, demonstrating the lasting impact of MAD Arts Academy\u2019s educational initiatives by transforming professional development into a public-facing, high-quality art
